review_body: Lens is what technology geeks not so long ago smugly chuckled at wishful thinking. It translates hand-written text, you can point it at almost anything and it'll tell you what it is, what you need to know about it, where you can buy it, [...]. However, as with any Google product: Be VERY aware that ...Full ReviewLens is what technology geeks not so long ago smugly chuckled at wishful thinking. It translates hand-written text, you can point it at almost anything and it'll tell you what it is, what you need to know about it, where you can buy it, [...]. However, as with any Google product: Be VERY aware that any interaction you have with Lens will be used to profile you, your behaviour and your mental state and this information will be sold indiscriminately.

I wanted to see if I could get it from Amazon, so I switched to the Amazon app. When I tried going back to the Lens app, it didn't show up in the list of recent apps, so I had to reopen the Lens app and rescan the part. My first scan must have been very lucky because this second attempt took many scans to finally get back to my initial result. For some strange reason, Google Lens does not show up in the list of previous apps, which is a pain when you need to switch between Lens and another app. Also, scanning the same thing multiple times produced very inconsistent results from scan to scan.
